      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "usp_Review_GetSBMRReviewerEmail",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to retrieve the email address of a reviewer associated with a specific SBMR (presumably \"Submission or Review\") reference number. It performs a query that joins two tables: "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "SBMR.SBMRHeader",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " and "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Membership.EC3Membership",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ", to find the email address of the reviewer whose authenticated user ID matches the one in the SBMR header record."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Low"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The procedure is straightforward, involving a single SELECT statement with an INNER JOIN between two tables. It uses a single input parameter to filter results, making it a low-complexity operation."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
